
Combiner
========


(0)

git clone --recursive https://github.com/johannessen/combiner


(1)
Install dependencies:

# Java 8 + Apache Ant + GDAL

# get GeoTools 17.0, <http://www.geotools.org/>
cd project/lib
# <http://sourceforge.net/projects/geotools/files/GeoTools%2017%20Releases/>
# geotools-17.0-bin.zip

# unpack into lib
unzip geotools-17.0-bin.zip

# get TestNG 6.8 (no other version tested)
# (currently there is trouble with certain releases; the one from the Internet Archive is known to be good, containing all required classes)

cd project/lib
curl -O "http://web.archive.org/web/20121113133417/http://testng.org/testng-6.8.zip"
unzip testng-6.8.zip
mv testng-6.8/testng-6.8.jar .
rm -R testng-6.8.zip testng-6.8

# get args4j 2.33, <http://args4j.kohsuke.org/>

cd project/lib
curl -O http://maven.jenkins-ci.org/content/repositories/releases/args4j/args4j/2.0.21/args4j-2.0.21.jar


# The class path consists of the lib directory and any _immediate_ subdirectories.


(2)
Install test dataset(s):

cd data
./testbed-nrw-prepare.sh


(3)
Build and run:

cd project
./run-combiner.sh

(Ant needs the current working directory set to project/ !)


Notes:
- "'on the fly' CRS transformation" needs to be enabled in QGIS's Project Properties, otherwise QGIS will ignore any CRS specified in the data.



osmium_to_spatiallite_test
==========================

dependency: osmium
